comments: Whiteside (POR) is firming up and makes slight contact with Oubre Jr.'s (PHX) during the pick.
Rubio (PHX) makes marginal contact with Whiteside (POR) during the rebound.
Anthony (POR) makes contact to Oubre Jr.'s (PHX) arm during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.  The contact from Anthony is prior to the block by Whiteside (POR).
During the rebound, Baynes (PHX) makes slight contact to Whiteside's (POR) arm as they come together for the loose ball.
Whiteside (POR) makes contact to Bridges' (PHX) arm during his shooting motion that affects his play at the basket.
Whiteside (POR) is firming up and makes slight contact to Rubio (PHX) while setting the pick.
Oubre Jr. (PHX) makes marginal contact to Lillard's (POR) arm on the driving shot attempt.
Baynes (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by Lillard (POR).

Johnson (PHX) and Lillard (POR) both make clean ball contact as they go for the loose ball on the rebound.  After communicating with the Replay Center, the call on the court of Portland ball is overturned.
Rubio (PHX) lowers his shoulder and delivers contact to Bazemore (POR) that dislodges him from his legal guarding position.
Rubio (PHX) slides his pivot foot.
Baynes (PHX) has a resting hand on Lillard's (POR) back during his driving shot attempt, but he does not apply any force before cleanly blocking the shot.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the call of goaltending by Baynes (PHX) is overturned as he blocks the shot before it touches the backboard on the driving shot attempt by Lillard (POR).
During the screen, Whiteside (POR) and Baynes (PHX) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Whiteside (POR) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Rubio's (PHX) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bazemore (POR) makes contact to Oubre Jr.'s (PHX) body after the release that affects his ability to land safely on his jump shot attempt.
Replay review of the blocking foul called on Baynes (PHX) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.
After the pick, McCollum (POR) and Oubre Jr. (PHX) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Kaminsky (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in McCollum's (POR) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Kaminsky (PHX) could be deemed to be in the lane for about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Anthony (POR) and Bridges (PHX) both legally go for the loose ball on the rebound.  The clock expires before the attempted take foul by Kaminsky (PHX).
